Heat oven to 450 degrees F. Season roast with salt and pepper. Place in shallow uncovered roasting pan. Roast 15 minutes. Meanwhile, stir together remaining ingredients. Spoon glaze over roast, spreading to cover. Reduce temperature to 350 degrees F. Return to oven and roast 45 minutes or until internal temperature reaches 145 degrees F. Place roast on a warm platter and cover for 10 minutes before slicing.